column4: Microsoft gives away more Office software to attract mobile users
column5: SEATTLE  Jan 29 Microsoft Corp made its popular Word  Excel and PowerPoint applications available for free on Android tablets on Thursday  marking the latest step in its drive to get as many mobile customers as possible using its software.

column4: US STOCKS SNAPSHOT-S&P 500 opens flat  Qualcomm weighs on Nasdaq
column5: NEW YORK  Jan 29 The S&P 500 opened little changed on Thursday  while the Dow rebounded after two days of sharp losses on strong labor market data  though weakness in Qualcomm shares in the wake of its results weighed on the Nasdaq.

column4: CORRECTED-US STOCKS-Futures rise with earnings after two days of losses  data due
column5: NEW YORK  Jan 29 U.S. stock index futures climbed on Thursday  rebounding after two days of sharp losses  ahead of housing and labor market data and another busy day for corporate earnings.
